Richard, For your information.  Take the total number of the people in the service from 1964 to 1975 (approx. ten million) and figure in the number of people that were in-country during those 11 years (three million) and you will see that the chances of being sent in country was about 1-in-3.  Or 33% of going versus 66% of being in the service and not being sent to South East Asia.
